-- 
MasterCard Names Cairns President of International Markets

-- B y   D o n a l   G r i f f i n
-- 
2011-06-28T13:30:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-28/mastercard-names-cairns-president-of-international-markets.html
MasterCard Inc. (MA) , the world’s second-
largest payments network, named Ann Cairns president of
international markets and Walt Macnee vice chairman.  Cairns will start on Aug. 22 from Alvarez & Marsal Inc., a
consulting company, and report to Chief Executive Officer  Ajay Banga , Purchase, New York-based MasterCard said today in a
statement. She will manage all markets and customer-related
activities outside the U.S., where MasterCard got 58 percent of
its revenue in 2010, according to Bloomberg data.  Cairns previously worked for Dutch lender ABN Amro Group NV
and  Citigroup Inc. (C) , the third-largest U.S. bank, MasterCard
said. She will replace Macnee, who had the job since 2008. He
will become vice chairman on Aug. 22 and handle “various senior
client and government relationships,” the company said.  “Ann is a proven leader with a track record of delivering
outstanding results,” Banga said in the statement. “Her
leadership, extensive financial-services expertise and global
experience will benefit our customers, and bring value to our
company.”  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Donal Griffin at 
 dgriffin10@bloomberg.net  